                  <h2 >How to use SharePod effectively?</h2>
                  <br>
                  <div class="lead ">
                     <ol style="line-height: 2;">
                           <li> Once on the Home Page, go to Sign Up and register your profile appropriately.</li>
     <li>Now, you can see your profile and the rooms that you are currently part of (none, at the moment).</li>
    <li>You can either Join a Room (Point 5) or Create a Room first. To create a room, Select a unique Room ID and Password yourself and remember it.</li>
    <li>Now you need to share with your friends or family, the Room ID that you just created along with the password so that they can access it using ‘Join Room’.</li>
    <li>In order to join a room, Enter the Room ID and Password that your friend just told you or the one that you created yourself to access the Room Page.</li>
    <li> Now, you can view the items or add some new items which you want to buy in the list easily using the graphical interface.</li>
    <li> To delete your own added items, click on the ‘Delete ’ button which will take you to another page with your items list. You can click on any part of the row except for the 'X' button to view the order details. Click on the ‘X’ button to delete the particular item and press on ‘Done’ to go back to the Room Page.</li>
    <li> When you are already at the supermarket and wish to buy some items for your friend, check the status of that item on the room page and click on the ‘Buy ’ button to proceed. It will show you all the items which have not been bought yet, and you can press on the ‘+’ button to indicate that you are buying that particular item.You can click on any part of the row except for the '+' button to view the order details.  Click on ‘Done’ when your selection is over.</li>
    <li>Now, you and your friend can see your name appearing with the status of that particular item as ‘already bought’ or ‘green’. Similarly others can use it in the same way for effective use.</li>
    <li>Keep in mind that once your added items show ‘green’ status, you need to delete them yourself in order to make the room list more clean and organised, since you don't need that item anymore.</li>
    <li>Due to Cookies and Sessions, you will be logged in till you explicitly ‘Log Out’ so that you don't need to make the hassle of logging in every single time you reload the website.</li>


                     </ol>
                     <h4>Share this Web App with your friends, family, and colleagues and do email us for telling your feedback or grievances.</h4>
